 Creating a drop-down menu on a website requires a bit of HTML and CSS, but it is a relatively simple process. Here's a step-by-step guide to creating a drop-down menu:

1. Create HTML for the drop-down menu:
```html
<ul class="dropdown">
  <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
  <li><a href="#">Products</a></li>
  <li><a href="#">Blog</a></li>
  <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
</ul>
```
Notice that we've added a `class="dropdown"` to the `<ul>` tag. This will be used to style the dropdown menu.

2. Create CSS for the drop-down menu:
```css
.dropdown {
  display: inline-block;
  list-style: none;
}

.dropdown li {
  padding-left: 20px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.dropdown li:hover > ul {
  display: block;
}

.dropdown li a {
  text-decoration: none;
  color: black;
}

.dropdown li a:hover {
  color: #fafafa;
  text-decoration: none;
}

.dropdown li:hover > ul {
  display: block;
}

.dropdown li ul li {
  padding-left: 20px;
  list-style: none;
}
```
The `.dropdown` class sets the display to `inline-block` and removes any list-style.

The `.dropdown li` class sets the padding and cursor to pointer.

The `.dropdown li:hover > ul` class sets the CSS for the dropdown menu when it is hovered over.

The `.dropdown li a` class sets the text-decoration and color to none.

The `.dropdown li a:hover` class sets the color to #fafafa and the text-decoration to none.

The `.dropdown li:hover > ul` class sets the CSS for the dropdown menu when it is hovered over.

The `.dropdown li ul li` class sets the padding and list-style to none.

3. Add the CSS to your website:
In your HTML code, add the `style=""` attribute after the `</head>` tag and before the `</body>` tag. This will add the CSS to your website.

4. Add the HTML for the drop-down menu:
In your HTML code, add the `<ul class="dropdown">` tag after the `<body>` tag and before the closing `</body>` tag. This will add the drop-down menu to your website.

5. Add the CSS for the drop-down menu:
In your HTML code, add the `.dropdown` class to the `ul` tag. This will apply the CSS to the drop-down menu.

6. Test the drop-down menu:
In your HTML code, add the `class="dropdown"` to the `li` tag. This will add the drop-down menu to the list items.

Test the drop-down menu by hovering over the list items. The dropdown menu should appear.

 To change the background color of a website's header, you can use CSS to style the element. Here's an example of how to do it:
```css
header {
  background-color: green;
}
```
You can also use the NAME_1() function to apply color to the element:
```css
header {
  background-color: NAME_1('green');
}
```
NAME_1() takes a color name as input and outputs the corresponding hex value. You can specify a color name like `red`, `yellow`, `blue`, `gray`, or `black`.

